    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Caspar Ursinus Velius (Linz, 25 February
                    1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> He praises the merits of their common friend, Georg von
                            Logau, whom he is happy to help.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15300225_5_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad eundem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Qua mecum <persName>Logus</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Georg von
                        Logau (ca. 1500–1553), humanist, protégé of the Thurzós, and Royal Secretary
                        of Ferdinand I from 1527. First Canon, later Provost of Wrocław, see more
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Erbe</hi> 1986, 338–339; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Grimm</hi> 1987, 117; <hi rend="smallcap">Lakatos</hi> 2007, 78–79, and
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Kasza</hi> 2012, 128.</note> noster sit iunctus
                    familiaritate, tu imprimis non ignoras. Is ea est morum suavitate, verborum
                        ubertate,<note xml:id="note.2">About his eloquence and poetry see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kasza</hi> 2014, 157–165.</note> facetiarum lepore
                    praeditus, ut non solum mihi, sed etiam omnibus aliis, qui eius usi sunt
                    familiaritate, merito debeat esse carissimus; et <choice>
                        <orig>hac</orig>
                        <supplied>hanc</supplied>
                    </choice> ob causam bene ei esse volo, et si qua possum aut munificentia, aut
                    humanitate eum prosequi, id certe mea sponte, non alicuius inductus hortatibus
                    libenter faciam, tuum quoque erit, plero vestra mutua coniunctione et studiorum
                    aequalitate, ut ornatum eum esse velis. Quod si volueris, facile poteris, dum
                    enim tuis illum inserveris historiis et ingenii illius suavitatem, virtutem et
                    doctrinam probaveris, non parum gloriae eius nomini adiicies. Vale et me
                    ama.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Lincio</placeName> 25. Februarii 1530.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
